---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABand from '../components/CTABand.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About GovHub: AI for Government Contractors"
  description="GovHub builds AI proposal software for government contractors, so small and mid-size firms can compete on quality against much larger teams."
 ogImage="/brand/page-graphics/about-basecamp-dusk@2x.png">
  <main class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'About', url: '/about/' }]} />

    <PageHero art="/brand/page-graphics/about-basecamp-dusk.svg">
      <header class="prose">
        <h1>About GovHub</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          GovHub is AI proposal software built specifically for government
          contractors, so a small team can compete on quality against firms many
          times its size.
        </p>
      </header>
    </PageHero>

    <article class="prose">

      <h2>The problem we're solving</h2>
      <p>
        Winning government work is disproportionately hard for small and mid-size
        firms. The same 50-to-500-page solicitation lands on a two-person shop and
        a large prime alike, but only one of them has a dedicated proposal team.
        The result is that good companies with the right capabilities lose to
        bigger companies with bigger proposal budgets. We think the best solution
        should win the contract, not the biggest proposal shop.
      </p>

      <h2>What we build</h2>
      <p>
        GovHub compresses the most time-consuming parts of a government response:
        shredding the solicitation into a compliance matrix, drafting narrative
        against the evaluation criteria, autofilling the standard forms, and
        reviewing for compliance before submission. The goal is simple: let a
        small team produce a compliant, competitive proposal in a fraction of the
        time, without cutting corners.
      </p>

      <img
        class="team-illo"
        src="/brand/illustrations/illo-team-standup.svg"
        alt="A small team planning their next proposal pursuit together"
        width="720"
        height="420"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />

      <h2>How we approach it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Government-specific, not general-purpose.</strong> Section L/M structure, FAR/DFARS awareness, and compliance are the design center, not a configuration afterthought.</li>
        <li><strong>Assistive, not autonomous.</strong> GovHub removes the blank page and the mechanical work; your team keeps ownership of strategy and final quality.</li>
        <li><strong>Honest by default.</strong> We'd rather tell you what the tool does and doesn't do than oversell it, the same standard we hold this site to.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Want to see how it works? Explore the <a href="/solutions/">platform</a>,
        try the free <a href="/solutions/compliance-matrix-generator/">compliance
        matrix generator</a>, or <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </article>

    <CTABand heading="Compete on quality, not headcount" sub="Start a free trial and put GovHub on your next solicitation." />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .team-illo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
  main { padding: 1rem 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .prose { max-width: 46rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
  h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
  li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
